<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in a state • in state</xh5><p> <i>in a state</i>—(followed by Infinitive) fit for smth.; mentally ready to do smth.: He went on thinking of her till he was almost <u>in a state</u> to drown himself in the little brook.</p><p> <i>in state—</i>1. with great pomp and ceremony: If he represented a first-class paper and wished to “save his face” he had better travel <u>in state</u>. 2. <i>(of a dead body)</i> ceremoniously exposed to view before burial <i>(in the phrase “lie in state”): </i>It was in this chamber he breathed his last; here he lay <u>in state</u>.</p> </entry>
